{"id": 3087002, "abstract": "The paper “The Importance of Convexity in Learning with Squared Loss” gave a lower bound on the sample complexity of learning with quadratic loss using a nonconvex function class. The proof contains an error. We show that the lower bound is true under a stronger condition that holds for many cases of interest.", "cluster": "3", "citations": [221618614, 236736803, 3086992], "references": [239666708, 3086721, 3086992, 220360940, 2295809, 222505227, 242529553, 222190436, 220570748, 2322859], "authors": ["Wee Sun Lee", "P.L. Bartlett", "R.C. Williamson"], "title": "Correction to “The Importance of Convexity in Learning With Squared Loss” [Sep 98 1974-1980]"}